What you need to know:  Omanyala is the Africa 100m record holder at 9.77 seconds while Kerley and Bednarek are the 2020 Tokyo Olympic Games silver medallists in 100m and 200m respectivelyKerley, who won men’s 200m in personal best 19.76 at last year’s Kip Keino Classic, has a personal best 9.84 from his silver medal exploits at 2020 Tokyo OlympicsTuwei disclosed that 2020 Tokyo Olympics silver medallists from Kenya, Ferguson Rotich (800m) and Timothy Cheruiyot (1,500m) are back to reclaim their titles